---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/sections/Hero.astro';
import SocialSidebar from '../components/ui/SocialSidebar.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }];

const jsonLD = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  description: 'AFJ Limited privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data under UK GDPR.',
  url: 'https://www.afjltd.co.uk/privacy-policy',
};
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="AFJ Limited privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data. GDPR compliant. Contact info@afjltd.co.uk for data enquiries."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  jsonLD={jsonLD}
>
  <SocialSidebar />

  <Hero title="Privacy Policy" subtitle="How we collect, use, and protect your personal information." />

  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-wide max-w-3xl prose prose-lg">
      <p class="text-afj-secondary"><strong>Last updated:</strong> February 2026</p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        AFJ Limited ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, store, and share your personal data when you use our website (www.afjltd.co.uk) or our transport services.
      </p>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        AFJ Limited is the data controller for the purposes of the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">We may collect the following types of personal data:</p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li><strong>Contact information:</strong> name, email address, phone number, postal address</li>
        <li><strong>Booking information:</strong> service type, dates, pick-up/drop-off locations, special requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Patient information:</strong> medical needs relevant to transport (for NEPTS services only)</li>
        <li><strong>Employment information:</strong> CV, qualifications, DBS check results (for job applicants)</li>
        <li><strong>Website usage data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited (via cookies, with your consent)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li>To provide our transport services and fulfil bookings</li>
        <li>To respond to your enquiries and quote requests</li>
        <li>To process job applications</li>
        <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations (including CQC requirements)</li>
        <li>To improve our website and services</li>
        <li>To send marketing communications (only with your explicit consent)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">We process your personal data on the following legal bases:</p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li><strong>Contract:</strong> to provide services you have requested</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> to comply with regulatory requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> to operate and improve our business</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> for marketing communications and non-essential cookies</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">5. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information with:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li>Local councils and NHS trusts (as required for contracted services)</li>
        <li>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) for regulatory compliance</li>
        <li>Our service providers (e.g., web hosting, email services) who process data on our behalf</li>
        <li>Law enforcement agencies if required by law</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which it was collected. Booking records are kept for 7 years for contractual and legal reasons. Website analytics data is retained for 26 months.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Rectify inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Erase your data (in certain circumstances)</li>
        <li>Restrict processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
        <li>Object to processing</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@afjltd.co.uk" class="text-afj-sky-blue hover:text-afj-accent">info@afjltd.co.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">8. Cookies</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Our website uses cookies. Essential cookies are necessary for the website to function. Analytics and marketing cookies are only placed with your consent via our cookie banner. You can manage your cookie preferences at any time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">9. Security</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorised access, loss, or destruction.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-afj-green">10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-afj-secondary">
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@afjltd.co.uk" class="text-afj-sky-blue hover:text-afj-accent">info@afjltd.co.uk</a></li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:01216891000" class="text-afj-sky-blue hover:text-afj-accent">0121 689 1000</a></li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> AFJ Business Center, 2-18 Forster Street, Nechells, Birmingham, B7 4JD</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-afj-secondary leading-relaxed">
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" class="text-afj-sky-blue hover:text-afj-accent" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
